jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.common Defines a Java object model for the common types that are shared across the different schemas within OVAL. 
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.definitions Defines a Java object model for the elements, types, and attributes that compose the OVAL Definitions. 
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.directives Defines a Java object model for the elements, types, and attributes that compose the OVAL Directives. 
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.esx

jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.macos   
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.mitre Defines a Java object model for the Mitre's additional information which is not part of the official schema. 
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.results Defines a Java object model for the elements, types, and attributes that compose the OVAL Results. 
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.sc Defines a Java object model for the elements, types, and attributes that compose the OVAL System Characteristics. 
jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.solaris Defines a Java object model for the OVAL Solaris components.

Classes in jp.go.aist.six.oval.model.common used by jp.go.aist.six.oval.core.repository
GeneratorType
          The Generator type defines an element that is used to hold information about when a particular OVAL document was compiled, what version of the schema was used, what tool compiled the document, and what version of that tools was used.

          The Class enumeration type defines the different classes of OVAL Definitions.

          The Datatype enumeration type defines the legal datatypes that are used to describe the values of individual entities.

          The Existence enumeration type defines acceptable existence values, which are used to determine a result based on the existence of individual components.

          The Family enumeration type is a listing of families that OVAL supports at this time.

          The MessageLevel enumeration type defines the different levels associated with a message.

          The Operation enumeration type defines acceptable operations.
OperatorEnumeration
          The Operator enumeration type defines acceptable operators.
RecurseDirectionEnumeration
          The RecurseDirectionEnumeration defines the direction to recurse, either 'up' to parent directories, or 'down' into child directories.
RecurseEnumeration
          The RecurseEnumeration defines how to recurse into the path entity, in other words what to follow during recursion.
RecurseFileSystemEnumeration
          The RecurseFileSystemEnumeration defines the file system limitation of any recursion, either 'local' limiting data collection to local file systems (as opposed to file systems mounted from an external system), or 'defined' to keep any recursion within the file system that the file_object (path+filename) has specified.
WindowsViewEnumeration
          The Windows view type enumeration.
